ds. Setting these changes in context it discusses implications for practitioners and the wider UK public health workforce. A lively and comprehensive review of policy change, Multidisciplinary public health: Understanding the development of the modern workforce concludes with a reflection on the new public health system under way in England, making useful comparisons with the rest of the UK. This is an invaluable resource for anyone with an interest in public health, including public health academics and relevant postgraduate students.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Feb 2023) 0aMedical policyzGreat Britain. 0aPublic healthzGreat Britain. 7aMEDICAL / Public Health.2bisacsh1 aDonaldson, Sir Liam, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFerguson, Katie, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aSim, Fiona, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertBristol UP/Policy Press Complete eBook-Package 2014z978311119634340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781447300342423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781447300342/original  a978-3-11-119634-3  Bristol UP/Policy Press Complete eBook-Package 2014b2014  aGBV-deGruyter-alles